# Verification & Validation — Leveled Gate

Run when the user asks to validate readiness, verify documentation, or start implementation. Evaluate **Level 1 → 11 in order**. **Do not evaluate or report on levels above the first failure.**

On any failed check: add or update a row in `open-questions.md` ([Open Questions](#open-questions)); do not hide gaps in prose.

## Process

1. Read cited artifacts for the current level only.
2. Mark each sub-check **Pass** / **Fail** with one-line evidence.
3. If any Fail → record open question(s), emit report ([Report format](#report-format)), **stop**.
4. If all Pass → proceed to next level.
5. After Level 11 Pass → report **Ready for `6-code/`**; first `BL-##` may use [08-backlog-implement.mdc](08-backlog-implement.mdc) pre-flight.

For ID/traceability detail while checking, use [06-traceability.mdc](06-traceability.mdc).

## Edit hygiene *(every structure update)*

- [ ] Interview completed and user confirmed
- [ ] Impact assessed per [structure.md — Flows](../consultation/structure.md#flows)
- [ ] Templates applied for new files
- [ ] Cross-references validated
- [ ] Open questions captured; summary with changed files presented
- [ ] `F##`, `UR-F##-##`, `FR-F##-##`, `NFR-##`, `ADR-##` consistent across files
- [ ] Feature **Status** per [03-feature-lifecycle.mdc](03-feature-lifecycle.mdc)
- [ ] Glossary terms linked on first use per file
- [ ] Mermaid updated where flows changed
- [ ] `6-code/` traceability updated if adopted and upstream changed materially

