## Level 1 — Scope foundation

**Question:** Are business scenarios, stakeholders, goals, and a features inventory in place that covers all goals, desires, and problems?

| Check | Pass when |
|-------|-----------|
| Stakeholders & goals | `1-scope/stakeholders-and-goals.md` has ≥1 `STK-##`, ≥1 `GOL-##`; constraints/assumptions/non-goals reviewed |
| Business scenarios | `1-scope/business-scenarios.md` has boundary table + ≥1 in-scope `SCN-##` (actor, trigger, goal, main flow) |
| Glossary | Key domain terms in `1-scope/glossary.md` |
| Features inventory | `1-scope/features-list.md` exists; every **Must** `GOL-##` and in-scope `SCN-##` maps to ≥1 `F##`; **Summary** reflects user-visible capability |
| Coverage | No Must goal or in-scope scenario lacks a feature row; non-goals respected per [02-features-list.mdc](02-features-list.mdc) |

**On fail:** `Q-S##` in **Scope** section.

---

## Level 2 — Feature specifications

**Question:** Do feature specs exist, align with the features list, and cover scope?

| Check | Pass when |
|-------|-----------|
| Files | Every **Must** `F##` in features-list has matching `2-features/F##_*.md` |
| List sync | Frontmatter ID, **Status**, `requires` ↔ features-list row and dependency diagram |
| Scope trace | Each Must spec has ≥1 `UR-F##-##` traced to `GOL-##` and/or `SCN-##`; **Traces to** links resolve |
| Summary ↔ UR | features-list **Summary** ↔ primary UR / **Overview** intent |
| Dependencies | **Requires** synced across frontmatter, Overview, dependency diagram; no cycles |

**On fail:** `Q-F##-##` (Features section) or `Q-S##` if scope gap.

**Gate:** Must **Must** `F##` rows at least **Specifying** with Overview + UR before Level 3.

---

## Level 3 — Solution strategy

**Question:** Is architecture strategy defined and relevant to available features?

| Check | Pass when |
|-------|-----------|
| Document | `3-arch/solution-strategy.md` exists and is not placeholder-only |
| Ready gate | All items in [04-solution-strategy.mdc — Ready checklist](04-solution-strategy.mdc#ready-checklist) pass |
| Feature relevance | Every **Must** `F##` appears in NFR **Features**, ADR **Affects**, or Overview **Trace** |
| No blockers | No open `Q-A##`; structural ADRs **Accepted** |

**On fail:** `Q-A##`.

---

## Level 4 — Building blocks & runtime views

**Question:** Are building blocks and runtime views connected to feature flows?

| Check | Pass when |
|-------|-----------|
| Building blocks | `3-arch/building-blocks.md` has L1 `BB-##` (~5–12); each lists **Features**; Level/Parent/Type set per [05-architecture-docs.mdc](05-architecture-docs.mdc) |
| Feature → FR → BB | Every `FR-F##-##` targets a `BB-##` or documented external |
| Runtime views | Cross-cutting/async/external flows in `runtime-views.md` as `RT-##`; participants map to `BB-##` or `(external)` |
| Feature flows | Each spec **Runtime flow** / **UI flow** references `FR-F##-##`; cross-feature paths covered by `RT-##` where needed |

**On fail:** `Q-A##`.

