## Level 7 — UI & screen readiness for design

**Question:** Is there enough UI/screen description at feature and architecture level to start design?

| Check | Pass when |
|-------|-----------|
| Feature UI | User-facing Must features have **UI flow** (screens, transitions, key states/errors) |
| UI inventory | `4-design/design-strategy.md` has **Assumptions and agreements**, **UI intent**, **Screen inventory** (Must-path `MCK-##`), and **Component inventory** (`CMP-##` with What/Looks/Behaves) |
| Design tokens | `4-design/library.md` holds design tokens only (no duplicate component catalog) |
| Architecture UI | NFRs/ADRs cover platform, offline, accessibility, or nav constraints affecting UI |
| Mockup index | `4-design/mockups.md` has **Layout (planned)** or spec rows for Must screens (`MCK-##` traced to `F##` / `FR`) |

**On fail:** `Q-D##` or `Q-F##-##`.

---

## Level 8 — User journeys

**Question:** Do user journeys cover all flows for all features and building-block logic?

| Check | Pass when |
|-------|-----------|
| Journey set | `4-design/user-journeys.md` has `JRN-##` for each Must end-to-end path |
| Feature coverage | Every Must **UI flow** step appears in ≥1 journey |
| BB/runtime | Steps that cross blocks, external systems, or async paths reflect `RT-##` / **Runtime flow** |
| Visual flow | Each journey **Visual flow** references valid `MCK-##` or explicit `—` for non-visual steps |

**On fail:** `Q-D##`.

---

## Level 9 — Mockups (SVGs)

**Question:** Are all user-visible views in journeys backed by mockups and linked in journey files?

| Check | Pass when |
|-------|-----------|
| Index | Every `MCK-##` in journeys exists in `mockups.md` |
| SVG | Each linked `MCK-##` resolves to `4-design/mockups/screens/MCK-##-*.svg` or explicit spec-only (`—`) per [10-design-mockups.mdc](10-design-mockups.mdc) |
| Journey links | Journey steps cite correct `MCK-##`; **Visual flow** uses only existing IDs |
| Orphans | No orphan SVGs; filename prefix matches ID; SVG well-formed; paths relative to `4-design/` |

**On fail:** `Q-D##`.

---

## Level 10 — Backlog & tests

**Question:** Does the backlog cover all features with order and tests?

| Check | Pass when |
|-------|-----------|
| Coverage | Every Must `FR-F##-##` maps to ≥1 `BL-##` with verifiable Given/When/Then AC |
| Order | `5-dev/backlog.md` has **Suggested implementation order** and dependency diagram |
| Tests | Each `BL-##` cites `TC-##`; matching rows in `5-dev/testing-plan.md` |
| Traceability | `5-dev/traceability.md` updated: `FR → BL → TC` for Must scope |

**On fail:** `Q-V##`.

---

## Level 11 — Open questions cleared for code

**Question:** Are all critical open questions resolved so implementation can start?

| Check | Pass when |
|-------|-----------|
| Scope–Design | No blocking rows in `open-questions.md` for Must scope (or each has explicit MVP stub documented in target doc **and** cited in relevant `BL-##` notes) |
| Feature blockers | No blocking `Q-F##-##` for Must features |
| Dev scaffold | `Q-V##` resolved or stubbed per [08-backlog-implement.mdc](08-backlog-implement.mdc) (e.g. `6-code/` path) |
| Feature status | Must features **Dev-ready** (or **In development** if BL already started) |

**On fail:** add/keep row in appropriate section; do **not** start `6-code/` until Pass.

